1.Place the input file and the mesh file in the same directory as the executable (isaac.exe) — i.e., the directory where the executable was created after running make.
In this case:
Input file: [NACA0012_Re_10000.dat]
Mesh file: [medium_zero_double.grd]

2.Open a terminal and navigate to the directory containing isaac.exe, the input file, and the mesh file before running the simulation.

3.To run the simulation execute the following command:
./isaac <NACA0012_Re_10000.dat> output

where:
-isaac is the executable
-NACA0012_Re_10000.dat is the input file
-output is the file where the program output (log/results) will be written